[31m-## [0.2.4] — 2026-04-25[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Added[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- **Structured-output decision agents.** Research Manager, Trader, and Portfolio[m
[31m-  Manager now use `llm.with_structured_output(Schema)` on their primary call[m
[31m-  and return typed Pydantic instances. Each provider's native structured-output[m
[31m-  mode is used (`json_schema` for OpenAI / xAI, `response_schema` for Gemini,[m
[31m-  tool-use for Anthropic, function-calling for OpenAI-compatible providers).[m
[31m-  Render helpers preserve the existing markdown shape so memory log, CLI[m
[31m-  display, and saved reports keep working unchanged. (#434)[m
[31m-- **LangGraph checkpoint resume** — opt-in via `--checkpoint`. State is saved[m
[31m-  after each node so crashed or interrupted runs resume from the last[m
[31m-  successful step. Per-ticker SQLite databases under[m
[31m-  `~/.axonai/cache/checkpoints/`. `--clear-checkpoints` resets them. (#594)[m
[31m-- **Persistent decision log** replacing the per-agent BM25 memory. Decisions[m
[31m-  are stored automatically at the end of `propagate()`; the next same-ticker[m
[31m-  run resolves prior pending entries with realised return, alpha vs SPY, and[m
[31m-  a one-paragraph reflection. Override path with `AXONAI_MEMORY_LOG_PATH`.[m
[31m-  Optional `memory_log_max_entries` config caps resolved entries; pending[m
[31m-  entries are never pruned. (#578, #563, #564, #579)[m
[31m-- **DeepSeek, Qwen (Alibaba DashScope), GLM (Zhipu), and Azure OpenAI**[m
[31m-  providers, plus dynamic OpenRouter model selection.[m
[31m-- **Docker support** — multi-stage build with separate dev and runtime images.[m
[31m-- **`scripts/smoke_structured_output.py`** — diagnostic that exercises the[m
[31m-  three structured-output agents against any provider so contributors can[m
[31m-  verify their setup with one command.[m
[31m-- **5-tier rating scale** (Buy / Overweight / Hold / Underweight / Sell) used[m
[31m-  consistently by Research Manager, Portfolio Manager, signal processor, and[m
[31m-  the memory log; Trader keeps 3-tier (Buy / Hold / Sell) since transaction[m
[31m-  direction is naturally ternary.[m
[31m-- **Pytest fixtures** — lazy LLM client imports plus placeholder API keys so[m
[31m-  the test suite runs cleanly without credentials. (#588)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Changed[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- **`backend_url` default is now `None`** rather than the OpenAI URL. Each[m
[31m-  provider client falls back to its native default. The previous default[m
[31m-  leaked the OpenAI URL into non-OpenAI clients (e.g. Gemini), producing[m
[31m-  malformed request URLs for Python users who switched providers without[m
[31m-  overriding `backend_url`. The CLI flow is unaffected.[m
[31m-- All file I/O passes explicit `encoding="utf-8"` so Windows users no longer[m
[31m-  hit `UnicodeEncodeError` with the cp1252 default. (#543, #550, #576)[m
[31m-- Cache and log directories moved to `~/.axonai/` to resolve Docker[m
[31m-  permission issues. (#519)[m
[31m-- `SignalProcessor` reads the rating from the Portfolio Manager's rendered[m
[31m-  markdown via a deterministic heuristic — no extra LLM call.[m
[31m-- OpenAI structured-output calls default to `method="function_calling"` to[m
[31m-  avoid noisy `PydanticSerializationUnexpectedValue` warnings emitted by[m
[31m-  langchain-openai's Responses-API parse path. Same typed result, no warnings.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Fixed[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- Empty memory no longer triggers fabricated past-lessons in agent prompts;[m
[31m-  the memory-log redesign makes this structurally impossible since only the[m
[31m-  Portfolio Manager consults memory and only when entries exist. (#572)[m
[31m-- Tool-call logging processes every chunk message, not just the last one, and[m
[31m-  memory score normalization handles empty score arrays. (#534, #531)[m
[31m-[m
